On Tuesday, March 09, 2004, at 12:29PM, Jason Thorpe <thorpej(-at-)wasabisystems.com> wrote:

>A helper sure makes it a LOT easier.  You just need someone to hold the 
>shifter steady while you thread the bolts and get them in place.  Then 
>you can tap the backing plate with a mallet and screwdriver, with the 
>not-quite-tight bolts providing some tension.

Somewhat related but for anyone removing the shift rod for cleaning (not for adjustment) use some tape to mark the position of the shift plate on the floor so you don't upset the positioning when you reinstall it.

